  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@JoeStark110 Thanks for the example. Very helpful!\r\n\r\nThe menu behavior only refine on a single value. The behavior of `refine` in this context is to remove the previously selected value and refine the new one.\r\n\r\nIf you want to select multiple value, you should use the [connectRefinementList](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/connectors/connectRefinementList.html). Its `refine` will also take one item at a time, but is cumulative. Also if you refine on a value that is already selected, it will unselect it. ",
    "created_at": "2018-05-02T15:09:02Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2910#issuecomment-386011601",
    "id": 386011601,
